parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, it can cause electrical system malfunctions, including failure of essential systems like air conditioning, heating, and lighting.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the battery warning light illuminates
the electrical system malfunctions
the air conditioning or heating system fails
the lights in the vehicle flicker or go out
smoke appears under the hood or in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including loss of power, failure of essential systems, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates
the electrical system malfunctions
the air conditioning or heating system fails
the lights in the vehicle flicker or go out
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the windows roll up and down on their own
the doors lock and unlock on their own.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Tipm module can cause a range of problems, including loss of power, failure of essential systems, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windows roll up and down on their own
the doors lock and unlock on their own
the air conditioning or heating system fails
the electrical system malfunctions
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing recalled vehicles can leave owners at risk of accidents or other safety issues due to faulty components.
symptoms: The owner is unable to get the recalled part repaired due to unavailability
the dealer is unable to provide a timeline for repair
the owner is forced to continue driving a vehicle with a known safety issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump mounting bracket can cause fuel vapors to leak into the cabin, posing a risk of explosion or fire, and potentially harming occupants.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline in the cabin
fuel vapor coming out of AC vents
fuel smell fading when fuel level reaches about 7/8 of a tank
fuel leak on top of the starboard fuel pump.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of hydraulic lifters can cause the engine to produce loud ticking or tapping noises, lead to poor engine performance, and potentially damage the camshaft, resulting in costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud ticking or tapping noises from the engine
especially when parked or on startup
flashing check engine light
bad fuel fumes
engine shutting off while driving
difficulty driving due to worry of breakdown.
